1
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:34,918
=Vanished Name=

2
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,894
=Episode 11=
(Who is Wen Yuxiu?)

3
00:01:39,160 --> 00:01:42,201
The night before we planned
to leave together,

4
00:01:43,520 --> 00:01:45,281
a big truck from the factory

5
00:01:47,320 --> 00:01:50,600
knocked me over while backing up.

6
00:01:51,641 --> 00:01:55,600
I screamed my lungs out,
but it just wouldn't stop.

7
00:01:57,201 --> 00:01:58,641
That truck

8
00:02:00,520 --> 00:02:02,720
was carrying a ton of bricks.

9
00:02:04,800 --> 00:02:06,080
And my legs

10
00:02:07,481 --> 00:02:08,401
got crushed.

11
00:02:10,361 --> 00:02:11,521
Was it really an accident?

12
00:02:21,281 --> 00:02:26,401
Oh, and Skinny came back to see me
before she left.

13
00:02:27,561 --> 00:02:30,281
(Qidaohezi Building Materials Factory, 1996)
I never asked your name

14
00:02:31,841 --> 00:02:33,561
or what you used to do.

15
00:02:35,121 --> 00:02:38,600
I don't care what your name was
or what you used to do.

16
00:02:40,801 --> 00:02:44,600
I know you want to be a better person

17
00:02:46,081 --> 00:02:48,561
and do meaningful things.

18
00:02:51,081 --> 00:02:53,920
Who you used to be
doesn't matter, right?

19
00:02:59,241 --> 00:03:02,640
I wanted to become a better person
together with you.

20
00:03:04,281 --> 00:03:05,841
But now I can't leave.

21
00:03:07,121 --> 00:03:10,241
I need you to do something for me now.

22
00:03:13,241 --> 00:03:13,961
I'm listening.

23
00:03:14,440 --> 00:03:20,040
I'll lend you my identity.
You go and be that better person.

24
00:03:26,320 --> 00:03:27,040
Take it.

25
00:03:36,920 --> 00:03:40,801
Who you used to be doesn't matter.
From now on,

26
00:03:41,841 --> 00:03:43,081
you are Zhou Yun.

27
00:03:43,720 --> 00:03:44,720
Ms. Zhou.

28
00:03:47,760 --> 00:03:49,760
Alright now, don't cry.

29
00:03:57,521 --> 00:03:58,521
I'm taking you with me.

30
00:03:59,440 --> 00:04:02,640
I'll get you out of here
even if you're in a wheelchair.

31
00:04:04,841 --> 00:04:10,521
Well, listen to me.
The world is a harsh place.

32
00:04:11,561 --> 00:04:13,920
My heart and my blood have gone cold.

33
00:04:15,681 --> 00:04:18,001
I'm frozen stiff. I can't leave anymore.

34
00:04:21,601 --> 00:04:23,520
You are my biggest hope.

35
00:04:27,721 --> 00:04:30,601
The year I married my husband,

36
00:04:31,041 --> 00:04:34,200
he took me to Shanghai,
to a big department store.

37
00:04:34,681 --> 00:04:36,400
All I wanted was a golden pen.

38
00:04:37,520 --> 00:04:40,241
I wanted to be a teacher
and grade students' homework.

39
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:47,561
Here, take it.

40
00:04:53,640 --> 00:04:54,320
It's too valuable.

41
00:04:54,320 --> 00:04:55,200
- I can't take it.
- Take it.

42
00:04:55,721 --> 00:04:57,681
If, and I mean...

43
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:02,241
If you become a real teacher,

44
00:05:03,840 --> 00:05:05,721
fulfill my wish for me

45
00:05:07,840 --> 00:05:11,121
and give this pen to a gifted child.

46
00:05:11,960 --> 00:05:15,121
Tell them it's from Ms. Zhou,

47
00:05:15,640 --> 00:05:17,280
to write their life story.

48
00:05:18,960 --> 00:05:22,361
From now on, your name is Zhou Yun.

49
00:05:23,080 --> 00:05:23,880
Ms. Zhou.

50
00:05:33,520 --> 00:05:34,020
Don't cry.

51
00:05:36,320 --> 00:05:36,820
Don't cry.

52
00:05:39,001 --> 00:05:39,681
Don't cry.

53
00:05:51,361 --> 00:05:53,640
Skinny left

54
00:05:55,280 --> 00:05:57,121
in the spring of 1996.

55
00:05:58,801 --> 00:06:02,681
The very next year,
my husband died of a brain hemorrhage.

56
00:06:04,921 --> 00:06:06,001
Twenty-seven years

57
00:06:08,161 --> 00:06:09,440
passed in a flash.

58
00:06:13,161 --> 00:06:16,161
I didn't know where she came from.

59
00:06:18,520 --> 00:06:21,080
But I know for sure she was a runaway.

60
00:06:23,280 --> 00:06:24,440
How can you be so sure?

61
00:06:26,840 --> 00:06:28,121
Wait for me.

62
00:06:35,440 --> 00:06:39,721
This is what she wore
when she came to the factory.

63
00:06:41,760 --> 00:06:45,561
I figure if she wasn't
desperate to escape,

64
00:06:45,840 --> 00:06:49,960
how could she run this far
in hospital gowns in the cold?

65
00:06:50,840 --> 00:06:52,301
- First People's Hospital.
- Note it down.

66
00:06:52,960 --> 00:06:58,520
She gave me these clothes
to keep as a memento.

67
00:06:58,880 --> 00:07:01,840
I don't know
if it'll help you solve the case.

68
00:07:02,520 --> 00:07:05,161
Thank you for your cooperation.
It's a crucial clue.

69
00:07:06,520 --> 00:07:10,161
Can we keep this as evidence
for safekeeping?

70
00:07:10,440 --> 00:07:13,041
Yeah, young lady, how about this?

71
00:07:13,041 --> 00:07:16,280
Please tell me if you hear anything
about Skinny, okay?

72
00:07:16,760 --> 00:07:18,601
Rest assured. It's our duty.

73
00:07:18,801 --> 00:07:20,041
We will do our best.

74
00:07:20,361 --> 00:07:21,921
Thank you.

75
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:27,780
Hello?

76
00:07:29,121 --> 00:07:30,741
Yanzi, go ahead.

77
00:07:32,640 --> 00:07:33,661
Alright, got it.

78
00:07:36,001 --> 00:07:36,921
What's up, Ma'am?

79
00:07:38,320 --> 00:07:40,801
Ms. Wang, the retired chemistry teacher,

80
00:07:41,121 --> 00:07:43,241
called us and said
that she has a lead to provide.

81
00:07:43,760 --> 00:07:44,472
Let's see her.

82
00:07:45,200 --> 00:07:49,121
We're here to learn about Zhou Yun.

83
00:07:50,280 --> 00:07:54,721
I was the last person at school
to see Ms. Zhou the day she left.

84
00:07:55,520 --> 00:07:58,200
I saw with my own eyes
that she took her files.

85
00:07:59,480 --> 00:08:03,608
(Qidaohezi Qidian Middle School, 2004)

86
00:08:12,721 --> 00:08:14,640
Ms. Zhou, don't you have classes?

87
00:08:15,760 --> 00:08:16,440
Ms. Wang.

88
00:08:17,960 --> 00:08:18,601
I'm transferred.

89
00:08:19,041 --> 00:08:20,921
Transferred? So sudden?

90
00:08:21,721 --> 00:08:23,681
No wonder you have your files.

91
00:08:24,361 --> 00:08:25,801
Something came up at home.

92
00:08:27,200 --> 00:08:28,152
Everything is okay?

93
00:08:29,080 --> 00:08:29,721
Yeah.

94
00:08:30,520 --> 00:08:32,961
Alright then. We'll keep in touch.

95
00:08:38,081 --> 00:08:38,680
Ms. Wang.

96
00:08:41,520 --> 00:08:44,280
Could I borrow your phone
to call my family?

97
00:08:45,280 --> 00:08:46,880
Sure, no problem.

98
00:08:48,040 --> 00:08:48,540
Here.

99
00:08:49,201 --> 00:08:50,640
(Do you still have that phone?)

100
00:08:51,160 --> 00:08:52,160
Last night,

101
00:08:53,121 --> 00:08:56,601
I searched all night
and actually managed to find it.

102
00:08:57,441 --> 00:08:59,721
I'm not sure if it'll be useful for you.

103
00:09:00,280 --> 00:09:01,081
Thank you so much.

104
00:09:02,001 --> 00:09:05,441
Give it to Tech Dept for data recovery.
See if they can find the call records.

105
00:09:05,760 --> 00:09:06,260
Got it.

106
00:09:06,800 --> 00:09:10,081
So Ge Wenjun didn't
report Ms. Zhou after she left.

107
00:09:10,441 --> 00:09:14,280
Ms. Zhou heard about it
before the letter even arrived.

108
00:09:14,721 --> 00:09:16,760
She thought her fake identity
had been exposed.

109
00:09:16,961 --> 00:09:19,201
That's why she rushed
to get the file and leave.

110
00:09:20,640 --> 00:09:24,280
So who tipped off Ms. Zhou
about the complaint beforehand?

111
00:09:24,721 --> 00:09:26,081
See how annoying big data is?

112
00:09:26,441 --> 00:09:28,441
It keeps pushing stuff
after I search for something.

113
00:09:28,441 --> 00:09:31,721
Author Liu Xiaoran
is sued by his wife Ren Xiaoming.

114
00:09:36,361 --> 00:09:39,601
Lawsuit alleging copyright infringement
in his new work opens today.

115
00:09:42,160 --> 00:09:42,680
Hello?

116
00:09:43,321 --> 00:09:45,640
Hello, Bai Shu, heard the news?

117
00:09:46,040 --> 00:09:48,520
Xiaoming is suing Liu Xiaoran.

118
00:09:49,040 --> 00:09:51,640
She can sue whoever she wants.
It's got nothing to do with me.

119
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:55,961
I just want to know if she'll dare
present the diary in court.

120
00:09:56,989 --> 00:09:59,625
(Wen's Shoe Shop, Erdaohezi)

121
00:10:01,976 --> 00:10:06,499
(Customized Leather Shoes)

122
00:10:08,121 --> 00:10:09,721
Welcome to Wen's Shoe Shop.

123
00:10:09,721 --> 00:10:11,241
- Shopping or customizing?
- Hello.

124
00:10:11,241 --> 00:10:12,601
I'd like to ask about someone.

125
00:10:13,361 --> 00:10:14,680
You're also here for Wen Yuxiu?

126
00:10:15,361 --> 00:10:16,081
Yeah.

127
00:10:16,441 --> 00:10:19,280
Someone came a couple of days ago.
Why's she suddenly so popular?

128
00:10:20,680 --> 00:10:22,081
They were helping me look for her.

129
00:10:23,321 --> 00:10:24,121
She was my teacher.

130
00:10:24,121 --> 00:10:25,520
I haven't seen her for years.

131
00:10:26,081 --> 00:10:28,001
- You came a long way, huh?
- Yeah.

132
00:10:28,001 --> 00:10:29,961
Hurry, sit down first.

133
00:10:29,961 --> 00:10:31,096
Let me get you some water.

134
00:10:31,560 --> 00:10:32,201
Thanks.

135
00:10:33,520 --> 00:10:34,020
Sit.

136
00:10:43,201 --> 00:10:46,880
This is Wen Yuxiu.
She's my kid's great-aunt.

137
00:11:01,201 --> 00:11:04,520
These are all our family photos.
Feel free to flip through them.

138
00:11:04,800 --> 00:11:06,821
Thanks. Go ahead with your work.

139
00:11:06,961 --> 00:11:07,461
Okay.

140
00:11:14,296 --> 00:11:16,024
(Wen Yuxiu and Ren Meiyan, July 1987)

141
00:11:23,560 --> 00:11:25,880
Excuse me, this is...

142
00:11:27,201 --> 00:11:29,280
This is Wen Yuxiu. Pretty, isn't she?

143
00:11:29,560 --> 00:11:32,841
Not just that. My mother-in-law
said she was a great student, too.

144
00:11:33,520 --> 00:11:35,800
She got into a university
down south, called...

145
00:11:36,680 --> 00:11:38,520
Well, anyway, it was really famous.

146
00:11:38,920 --> 00:11:41,640
But she didn't go.
Her dad wasn't in good health.

147
00:11:42,961 --> 00:11:45,760
She just attended
a local Teachers College.

148
00:11:46,520 --> 00:11:47,160
What a waste.

149
00:11:47,880 --> 00:11:49,001
The one next to her...

150
00:11:50,121 --> 00:11:53,841
I don't know her.
A classmate from the Teachers College?

151
00:11:54,280 --> 00:11:56,841
It was taken in 1987,
right when she was at Teachers College.

152
00:12:02,441 --> 00:12:03,280
Who is Wen Yuxiu?

153
00:12:06,800 --> 00:12:08,800
Why are you leaving everything
to a stranger?

154
00:12:25,321 --> 00:12:26,241
None of your business.

155
00:12:43,800 --> 00:12:45,121
(Wen Yuxiu and Ren Meiyan, July 1987)

156
00:12:45,121 --> 00:12:48,680
(Ren Meiyan,
so you knew Ms. Zhou all along?)

157
00:12:50,081 --> 00:12:53,640
(Why have you been
keeping it secret all this time?)

158
00:12:57,520 --> 00:12:58,321
Joker.

159
00:13:00,520 --> 00:13:01,201
Pass.

160
00:13:01,721 --> 00:13:02,321
Pass?

161
00:13:02,321 --> 00:13:03,001
Too big.

162
00:13:03,001 --> 00:13:04,121
All you pass, huh?

163
00:13:05,680 --> 00:13:08,640
Seven to Jack, five pairs.

164
00:13:13,721 --> 00:13:16,040
Pair of threes. The Landlord won.

165
00:13:17,040 --> 00:13:17,920
Your mom won again.

166
00:13:17,920 --> 00:13:18,841
Get a sticky note.

167
00:13:18,841 --> 00:13:21,121
You get flicked on the forehead
and get a sticky note.

168
00:13:22,520 --> 00:13:24,520
- How did we lose again?
- Let's sort this out.

169
00:13:25,361 --> 00:13:26,280
Li Meng.

170
00:13:26,961 --> 00:13:29,800
Auntie, it's so lively there.

171
00:13:30,520 --> 00:13:32,400
Playing cards?
Are you winning or losing?

172
00:13:32,880 --> 00:13:34,601
We're not playing for money.

173
00:13:36,121 --> 00:13:39,560
Auntie. I was hoping
you could help me with something.

174
00:13:40,721 --> 00:13:44,520
Xiaoming said that you worked
in the People's Hospital.

175
00:13:45,201 --> 00:13:48,520
Could you take a look
at this hospital gown?

176
00:13:49,520 --> 00:13:52,520
Can you tell which era this is from?

177
00:13:53,040 --> 00:13:56,001
And can you tell
which department it belongs to?

178
00:14:11,841 --> 00:14:12,760
Can you tell?

179
00:14:17,201 --> 00:14:17,760
Auntie?

180
00:14:20,520 --> 00:14:22,361
- What happened?
- Why did she hang up?

181
00:14:23,441 --> 00:14:25,880
Mom, what's wrong?

182
00:14:29,520 --> 00:14:30,201
What happened?

183
00:14:31,640 --> 00:14:34,520
Mom, come on. Let's keep playing.

184
00:14:34,920 --> 00:14:35,441
Keep playing.

185
00:14:36,920 --> 00:14:37,441
Mom.

186
00:14:37,680 --> 00:14:38,321
Meiyan.

187
00:14:38,400 --> 00:14:39,241
Mom, what's wrong?

188
00:14:40,001 --> 00:14:40,640
(Defendant, Defendant's Attorney)
Your Honor.

189
00:14:40,880 --> 00:14:43,400
My client can't make it
due to unforeseen circumstances.

190
00:14:43,520 --> 00:14:45,241
We request an adjournment.

191
00:14:45,680 --> 00:14:47,841
Does the defense
agree to the adjournment?

192
00:14:50,920 --> 00:14:52,841
Your Honor,
we do not agree to an adjournment.

193
00:14:56,560 --> 00:14:57,208
Court adjourned.

194
00:15:01,640 --> 00:15:05,241
Ma'am, the person
Zhou Yun last contacted was Ren Meiyan.

195
00:15:06,721 --> 00:15:07,560
Ren Xiaoming's mom?

196
00:15:07,920 --> 00:15:10,160
Yeah, the data recovery

197
00:15:10,520 --> 00:15:13,400
showed the number Zhou Yun dialed
was a PHS number.

198
00:15:13,880 --> 00:15:17,800
According to telecom records,
the owner of that number is Ren Meiyan.

199
00:15:19,601 --> 00:15:21,361
In such an urgent situation,

200
00:15:22,201 --> 00:15:25,400
why would she call the parent
of a student who had already graduated?

201
00:15:26,160 --> 00:15:29,361
Yeah, this is weird.

202
00:15:31,241 --> 00:15:31,760
Yanzi.

203
00:15:33,800 --> 00:15:34,920
Let's talk to Ren Meiyan.

204
00:15:35,601 --> 00:15:36,101
Okay.

205
00:15:39,961 --> 00:15:42,808
My place is small. We can't talk there,
so I asked you to meet me here.

206
00:15:44,841 --> 00:15:46,880
Wen Yuxiu and I
attended the same Teachers College.

207
00:15:47,160 --> 00:15:51,321
(La City, 1987)

208
00:15:51,321 --> 00:15:52,680
Yuxiu, come here.

209
00:15:53,201 --> 00:15:53,701
Meiyan.

210
00:15:54,241 --> 00:15:54,741
Come on.

211
00:15:57,721 --> 00:15:58,241
Look.

212
00:15:59,880 --> 00:16:01,520
I brought you braised pork.

213
00:16:01,920 --> 00:16:03,280
No need, I brought food.

214
00:16:04,441 --> 00:16:06,081
Pickles aren't nutritious.

215
00:16:06,520 --> 00:16:10,880
Look at your face.
You're so pale. Dig in.

216
00:16:11,961 --> 00:16:13,560
Why are you giving it all to me?

217
00:16:14,560 --> 00:16:16,520
Silly girl, you forgot?
We run a butcher business.

218
00:16:16,680 --> 00:16:20,160
I'm sick of pork.
You're so thin. Eat more.

219
00:16:21,961 --> 00:16:25,160
Fine, I'll make you leather shoes
as a gift when I go home.

220
00:16:27,040 --> 00:16:28,520
You know how to make leather shoes?

221
00:16:28,961 --> 00:16:29,961
Didn't you know?

222
00:16:30,280 --> 00:16:32,280
Wen's Shoe Shop in Erdaohezi.

223
00:16:32,520 --> 00:16:36,081
I learned shoemaking from my dad
since I was little. I'm skilled.

224
00:16:38,640 --> 00:16:40,920
Then I want a pair of high-heels.

225
00:16:43,640 --> 00:16:48,721
A calendar girl wore high heels
with bell-bottoms. It's fantastic.

226
00:16:49,560 --> 00:16:51,841
Give me the calendar.
I'll make them just like that.

227
00:16:52,520 --> 00:16:54,040
I want white leather shoes too.

228
00:16:55,400 --> 00:16:56,441
White shoes?

229
00:16:58,321 --> 00:17:00,520
I'll need leftover leather
from customers.

230
00:17:00,841 --> 00:17:02,680
Few customers order white leather shoes.

231
00:17:03,001 --> 00:17:06,280
I'm joking. Use whatever color you have.

232
00:17:06,840 --> 00:17:09,600
Mixing all colors is more fashionable.

233
00:17:14,241 --> 00:17:15,840
Can you ask for leave for me later?

234
00:17:17,040 --> 00:17:18,161
You're going out again?

235
00:17:18,800 --> 00:17:21,360
Zhao Ding is picking me up.
We're going to a movie.

236
00:17:23,681 --> 00:17:25,681
Take my lunchbox back. See you.

237
00:17:26,401 --> 00:17:26,921
Meiyan.

238
00:17:29,401 --> 00:17:30,551
What's wrong?

239
00:17:32,664 --> 00:17:35,520
Go ahead. Come back early. Be careful.

240
00:17:36,201 --> 00:17:36,760
Got it.

241
00:17:40,201 --> 00:17:40,881
Come on.

242
00:17:47,881 --> 00:17:50,840
(Back then, I was love-struck
with Xiaoming's dad.)

243
00:17:51,800 --> 00:17:53,881
(She kept persuading me to study.)

244
00:17:53,881 --> 00:17:55,241
(But I couldn't listen.)

245
00:17:56,201 --> 00:17:57,800
Young people are all the same.

246
00:17:59,080 --> 00:18:02,360
But I should have listened to her.
If only I had listened.

247
00:18:03,441 --> 00:18:04,840
One wrong step leads to many.

248
00:18:05,600 --> 00:18:09,401
The biggest mistake
was going south with Xiaoming's dad.

249
00:18:14,080 --> 00:18:14,641
Meiyan.

250
00:18:21,961 --> 00:18:23,520
What happened?

251
00:18:24,881 --> 00:18:25,881
I'm going to Guangdong.

252
00:18:26,320 --> 00:18:27,520
What about school?

253
00:18:29,881 --> 00:18:32,401
My family hosted a dinner that day.
A cattle butcher came.

254
00:18:32,800 --> 00:18:33,881
He brought his son.

255
00:18:34,560 --> 00:18:37,760
Turns out it was a matchmaking setup.
My parents like the young man.

256
00:18:38,360 --> 00:18:41,161
They want us to get engaged next month
and get married by the end of the year.

257
00:18:41,161 --> 00:18:42,520
But you're still in school.

258
00:18:43,120 --> 00:18:44,921
They said, "Quit studying.

259
00:18:46,001 --> 00:18:49,360
A school teacher makes less money
than someone washing pig intestines."

260
00:18:50,560 --> 00:18:51,760
How can they say that?

261
00:18:52,441 --> 00:18:54,280
I'll go back with you and talk to them.

262
00:18:54,961 --> 00:18:55,560
Forget it.

263
00:18:56,760 --> 00:19:00,520
Even if I refuse this marriage,
they won't approve of Zhao Ding.

264
00:19:05,600 --> 00:19:07,320
My mom says he isn't reliable.

265
00:19:12,241 --> 00:19:14,360
But I like him and want to be with him.

266
00:19:16,520 --> 00:19:17,921
Then what can you do?

267
00:19:19,600 --> 00:19:21,120
I have to leave with him.

268
00:19:24,201 --> 00:19:26,881
It's okay. I'll get you some money.

269
00:19:28,040 --> 00:19:30,600
Yuxiu, I just need money
for a train ticket.

270
00:19:31,800 --> 00:19:34,401
That's not enough.
What will you eat and drink there?

271
00:19:34,881 --> 00:19:37,241
When I get there and earn money,
I'll pay you back.

272
00:19:38,040 --> 00:19:39,080
I swear.

273
00:19:39,760 --> 00:19:42,001
Forget about that. Wait here.

274
00:19:47,560 --> 00:19:50,520
This is her when she was young.
See how pretty she is?

275
00:19:52,520 --> 00:19:53,320
You look nice too.

276
00:19:57,441 --> 00:19:59,080
I meant to repay Yuxiu.

277
00:20:01,080 --> 00:20:02,520
But it wasn't easy to make money.

278
00:20:03,060 --> 00:20:03,560
I regret it

279
00:20:03,560 --> 00:20:04,820
every time I think about it.

280
00:20:04,820 --> 00:20:06,881
She ended up like this
because I took her money.

281
00:20:06,881 --> 00:20:09,161
I ruined her. I ruined her whole life.

282
00:20:11,681 --> 00:20:14,520
She helped me escape,
but she had nowhere to run.

283
00:20:16,536 --> 00:20:18,360
(Wen's Shoe Shop, Erdaohezi, 1987)

284
00:20:18,360 --> 00:20:19,961
Auntie, where's my dad?

285
00:20:20,641 --> 00:20:22,961
At the hospital. He had another attack.

286
00:20:23,280 --> 00:20:25,921
The doctor said
he must have surgery this time.

287
00:20:26,360 --> 00:20:28,520
Otherwise, he won't make it.

288
00:20:29,641 --> 00:20:30,552
Where are you going?

289
00:20:31,120 --> 00:20:31,760
To the hospital.

290
00:20:32,320 --> 00:20:35,120
Will that give your dad
the money for surgery?

291
00:20:36,721 --> 00:20:37,241
Come on.

292
00:20:39,040 --> 00:20:39,600
Yuxiu.

293
00:20:40,760 --> 00:20:44,120
This is Hao Ying,
a technician from our Qidaohezi Farm.

294
00:20:44,681 --> 00:20:45,520
Meet each other.

295
00:20:49,641 --> 00:20:51,520
Hello, I'm Hao Ying.

296
00:21:09,961 --> 00:21:12,280
Your aunt said you were looking for me?

297
00:21:15,120 --> 00:21:16,401
Promise me three things.

298
00:21:16,881 --> 00:21:17,760
Then I'll marry you.

299
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:20,520
Tell me.

300
00:21:21,201 --> 00:21:25,280
First, pay for my dad's surgery
and support him until his passing.

301
00:21:26,520 --> 00:21:28,641
Second, let me finish school.

302
00:21:31,800 --> 00:21:32,560
Third,

303
00:21:34,840 --> 00:21:38,520
I want half a piece
of top-grade lambskin that is white.

304
00:21:41,120 --> 00:21:42,681
Okay, no problem.

305
00:22:42,641 --> 00:22:45,001
So, my teacher lent all her money out

306
00:22:45,560 --> 00:22:47,520
and married someone out of desperation.

307
00:22:48,120 --> 00:22:50,001
They still haven't paid back yet.

308
00:22:50,641 --> 00:22:52,840
How immoral are those people?

309
00:22:54,280 --> 00:22:58,280
I'm telling you, marriage can truly
change a woman's fate.

310
00:22:58,921 --> 00:23:02,520
She married a guy named Hao Ying.
At first, he treated her well.

311
00:23:03,201 --> 00:23:04,080
He was also

312
00:23:04,520 --> 00:23:06,520
looking after her dad in the sickbed.

313
00:23:08,001 --> 00:23:10,921
But you know,
who can predict life and death?

314
00:23:11,961 --> 00:23:15,280
That old man passed away
on the Chinese New Year's Eve.

315
00:23:19,760 --> 00:23:23,001
Brother, how could you just leave?

316
00:23:28,560 --> 00:23:31,161
Yuxiu, don't accuse me
of being heartless.

317
00:23:31,641 --> 00:23:35,241
We can't have a funeral
during the Spring Festival.

318
00:23:37,520 --> 00:23:39,641
Alright, let's go.

319
00:23:40,800 --> 00:23:43,161
Auntie, those leather shoes of mine...

320
00:23:43,600 --> 00:23:44,641
Aren't they from the shop?

321
00:23:44,800 --> 00:23:46,241
I bought the leather for Yuxiu.

322
00:23:48,401 --> 00:23:50,520
Erwenzi, bring me
those white leather shoes.

323
00:24:10,520 --> 00:24:13,040
(Then, Hao Ying took Wen Yuxiu
back to his hometown.)

324
00:24:20,803 --> 00:24:24,795
(Tubao Village)

325
00:24:57,961 --> 00:25:00,020
Yuxiu, we're here.

326
00:25:03,001 --> 00:25:03,560
Right here.

327
00:25:10,760 --> 00:25:11,260
Here.

328
00:25:28,760 --> 00:25:31,201
Come on, let's go inside.

329
00:25:47,600 --> 00:25:49,421
Right here, come on.

330
00:25:51,760 --> 00:25:53,501
Come on, get inside.

331
00:26:06,881 --> 00:26:08,201
This is our old house.

332
00:26:09,441 --> 00:26:12,280
Nobody's lived here for years.
It's okay, right?

333
00:26:12,961 --> 00:26:14,520
My parents are with my brother.

334
00:26:16,201 --> 00:26:18,921
This house is just for us.
This is our home.

335
00:26:19,721 --> 00:26:21,280
See those two rundown sheds?

336
00:26:21,600 --> 00:26:23,080
I'll fix them up once we're settled.

337
00:26:23,760 --> 00:26:28,320
We'll raise some cows, sheep,
and livestock like that.

338
00:26:29,001 --> 00:26:30,881
Then we will have a bunch of babies.

339
00:26:32,280 --> 00:26:35,681
We'll live a stable life here
for the rest of our days.

340
00:27:43,032 --> 00:27:45,656
(Wen's Shoe Shop)

341
00:28:21,040 --> 00:28:22,120
(Without a steady job,)

342
00:28:22,600 --> 00:28:25,881
(Hao Ying had no stable income
in his hometown.)

343
00:28:26,201 --> 00:28:28,161
All you do all day is reading.

344
00:28:28,280 --> 00:28:30,961
(The less money he had,
the worse his temper got.)

345
00:28:31,441 --> 00:28:33,641
What's the point of reading?
Who do you think you are?

346
00:28:33,881 --> 00:28:34,600
Come with me.

347
00:28:35,241 --> 00:28:35,881
What for?

348
00:28:36,120 --> 00:28:37,520
To make babies. What do you think?

349
00:28:38,264 --> 00:28:38,840
(Obstetrics and Gynecology)

350
00:28:38,840 --> 00:28:41,980
(Qidaohezi People's Hospital, 1992)

351
00:28:44,881 --> 00:28:45,600
Li Hui?

352
00:28:45,921 --> 00:28:46,520
Over here.

353
00:28:49,641 --> 00:28:50,280
Meiyan?

354
00:29:33,441 --> 00:29:36,320
Meiyan, why did you
come back from Guangzhou?

355
00:29:36,560 --> 00:29:37,760
Well, I'm pregnant again.

356
00:29:38,360 --> 00:29:40,881
I can't afford to raise two kids
in Guangzhou.

357
00:29:42,280 --> 00:29:43,280
Why did you come back?

358
00:29:45,080 --> 00:29:48,080
I went for a check-up.
The baby is in the wrong position.

359
00:29:48,560 --> 00:29:51,641
The local doctors said
I must give birth in a big hospital.

360
00:29:52,401 --> 00:29:54,961
So I came back.
I'll run away after giving birth.

361
00:29:56,760 --> 00:29:59,881
Meiyan, I must find a chance
to escape this time.

362
00:30:00,320 --> 00:30:01,760
I can't let him catch me again.

363
00:30:03,080 --> 00:30:06,401
Okay, tell me your plan. I'll help you.

364
00:30:07,800 --> 00:30:12,001
But I... I used up all the money
when Xiaoming was last hospitalized.

365
00:30:12,201 --> 00:30:13,800
I don't have any money on me now.

366
00:30:15,681 --> 00:30:18,161
I know, you must be worse off than me.

367
00:30:19,080 --> 00:30:22,201
Don't worry about the money.
I'll figure something out.

368
00:30:22,600 --> 00:30:26,001
Yuxiu, I owe you too much.

369
00:30:43,161 --> 00:30:45,481
(Wen's Shoe Shop, Erdaohezi,2023)
The baby girl died from

370
00:30:46,001 --> 00:30:47,161
a cord around the neck.

371
00:30:49,001 --> 00:30:52,681
Then Yuxiu ran away,
and Hao Ying went looking for her.

372
00:30:53,320 --> 00:30:56,320
They say the child
was left at the hospital.

373
00:30:57,320 --> 00:30:58,360
He didn't even bother.

374
00:31:02,040 --> 00:31:04,360
Anyway, Hao Ying didn't want daughters.

375
00:31:05,001 --> 00:31:06,721
By the time I saw her again,

376
00:31:08,760 --> 00:31:10,681
she was already
Xiaoming's homeroom teacher.

377
00:31:11,128 --> 00:31:15,542
(Qidaohezi, 2004)

378
00:31:27,161 --> 00:31:28,401
Don't turn on the light.

379
00:31:33,040 --> 00:31:34,080
Let me pour you some tea.

380
00:31:35,961 --> 00:31:37,681
No, forget it.

381
00:31:38,080 --> 00:31:39,000
The water is inside.

382
00:31:39,201 --> 00:31:39,721
Meiyan.

383
00:31:42,080 --> 00:31:42,800
Have some water.

384
00:31:43,241 --> 00:31:44,481
Meiyan, stop fussing.

385
00:31:44,881 --> 00:31:46,721
Let's talk before the kids come back.

386
00:31:47,881 --> 00:31:48,920
Where did you come from?

387
00:31:49,560 --> 00:31:50,161
The school.

388
00:31:50,560 --> 00:31:51,241
The school?

389
00:31:51,760 --> 00:31:53,401
I'm Xiaoming's homeroom teacher now.

390
00:31:54,360 --> 00:31:56,600
Xiaoming's homeroom teacher is Ms. Zhou.

391
00:31:57,201 --> 00:31:59,520
That's me. I'm Zhou Yun now.

392
00:32:01,320 --> 00:32:02,600
How come you're Zhou Yun?

393
00:32:03,641 --> 00:32:05,241
Where have you been all these years?

394
00:32:08,120 --> 00:32:11,881
Auntie, what did Wen Yuxiu
say on the phone

395
00:32:12,040 --> 00:32:14,721
when she left Qidian Middle School?

396
00:32:15,760 --> 00:32:19,320
She said she was getting reported
and had to leave.

397
00:32:22,241 --> 00:32:23,921
Did you contact each other again?

398
00:32:26,721 --> 00:32:30,161
She didn't leave any contact info.
I thought about going to the police.

399
00:32:31,401 --> 00:32:35,201
But then I thought, maybe the police
were looking for her too.

400
00:32:36,401 --> 00:32:38,881
If I went to the police,
it would expose her identity.

401
00:32:40,641 --> 00:32:41,520
So I waited.

402
00:32:43,161 --> 00:32:46,080
As long as she's alive,
she will come back to see me.

403
00:32:48,401 --> 00:32:48,921
Auntie.

404
00:32:50,001 --> 00:32:53,280
Do you know
where Wen Yuxiu's husband lives?

405
00:32:54,001 --> 00:32:54,760
I have no idea.

406
00:32:54,921 --> 00:32:55,560
No contact?

407
00:32:55,921 --> 00:32:56,560
No.

408
00:32:56,881 --> 00:32:59,320
Did she ever write any letters?

409
00:33:00,001 --> 00:33:04,161
Actually, she did.
Let me find them for you.

410
00:33:04,241 --> 00:33:05,040
Alright.

411
00:33:14,080 --> 00:33:14,881
Here.

412
00:33:17,760 --> 00:33:19,360
Qingjiang Province, Shabei County,

413
00:33:19,360 --> 00:33:21,161
(To: Wen Guilan)
Xinglong Town, Tubao Village.

414
00:33:21,721 --> 00:33:22,721
Isn't this the address?

415
00:33:23,760 --> 00:33:25,840
But this letter was sent in 2004.

416
00:33:26,080 --> 00:33:29,360
They lived there back then.
Who knows where they live now?

417
00:33:30,481 --> 00:33:31,641
Can I keep this letter?

418
00:33:31,961 --> 00:33:34,080
Take it. It's no use to me.

419
00:33:34,280 --> 00:33:34,881
Thank you.

420
00:33:36,161 --> 00:33:37,241
Keep it as a memento.

421
00:33:37,464 --> 00:33:42,008
(Customized Leather Shoes)

422
00:33:51,201 --> 00:33:54,080
(I found Ms. Zhou.
Her real name is Wen Yuxiu.)

423
00:34:06,241 --> 00:34:08,680
Ma'am, I just checked the name
you gave me.

424
00:34:09,080 --> 00:34:11,921
Wen Yuxiu has a deposit
of over 30,000 yuan

425
00:34:11,921 --> 00:34:13,321
at the Agricultural Cooperative Bank.

426
00:34:13,321 --> 00:34:15,761
But the money was withdrawn
all at once in 2004.

427
00:34:16,160 --> 00:34:19,321
However, it was someone named Hao Ying
who withdrew it on her behalf.

428
00:34:20,240 --> 00:34:21,401
Hao Ying?

429
00:35:01,496 --> 00:35:03,504
(Certificate of Honor)

430
00:35:09,176 --> 00:35:14,104
(Agricultural Cooperative Bank
Deposit Slip, Wen Yuxiu)

431
00:35:26,640 --> 00:35:28,040
You're back without telling me?

432
00:35:33,160 --> 00:35:34,200
What are you looking for?

433
00:35:40,520 --> 00:35:41,881
I didn't know who she was.

434
00:35:43,281 --> 00:35:45,281
I only knew
you kept this piece of paper.

435
00:35:46,640 --> 00:35:47,801
Now I finally know.

436
00:35:52,280 --> 00:35:52,961
(Qidaohezi, 2004)

437
00:35:52,961 --> 00:35:57,640
(In September 2004, I went to
the Agricultural Cooperative Bank)

438
00:35:58,441 --> 00:35:59,881
(and happened to see Zhou Yun.)

439
00:36:01,040 --> 00:36:04,361
(She looked flustered and suspicious.)

440
00:36:05,040 --> 00:36:06,361
(So I took a closer look.)

441
00:36:08,001 --> 00:36:09,921
(Sure enough, I found a problem.)

442
00:36:12,881 --> 00:36:13,401
Hello.

443
00:36:13,720 --> 00:36:15,160
I'd like to make a deposit.

444
00:36:29,281 --> 00:36:30,761
(Her name wasn't Zhou Yun.)

445
00:36:30,761 --> 00:36:31,881
(Agricultural Cooperative Bank
Deposit Slip, Wen Yuxiu).

446
00:36:31,881 --> 00:36:34,881
(Her real name was Wen Yuxiu.)

447
00:36:35,481 --> 00:36:38,761
(She was impersonating someone
and had forged her credentials.)

448
00:36:40,568 --> 00:36:43,224
(500 yuan)

449
00:37:21,961 --> 00:37:22,720
Wen Yuxiu.

450
00:37:28,281 --> 00:37:29,881
I've written a complaint letter.

451
00:37:30,441 --> 00:37:34,600
Whoever takes my daughter
away from me will pay.

452
00:37:36,761 --> 00:37:37,481
You're finished.

453
00:37:49,560 --> 00:37:54,361
Reporting her should have been enough.
Why did you threaten her?

454
00:37:54,881 --> 00:37:56,240
Because I wanted her to know

455
00:37:57,560 --> 00:37:59,080
that I was the one punishing her.

456
00:38:08,640 --> 00:38:11,680
Take a look. This is
Wen Yuxiu's deposit in Qidaohezi.

457
00:38:12,240 --> 00:38:13,401
Did you know about this?

458
00:38:29,160 --> 00:38:31,921
This is a small computer. Look into it.

459
00:38:31,921 --> 00:38:33,160
Develop your brain.

460
00:38:33,720 --> 00:38:34,481
It's for me?

461
00:38:34,720 --> 00:38:35,401
It's for you.

462
00:38:36,801 --> 00:38:37,680
Hello? Who is this?

463
00:38:38,321 --> 00:38:39,720
Hello, Meiyan? It's me.

464
00:38:42,560 --> 00:38:43,680
Wait, I'll go outside.

465
00:38:47,761 --> 00:38:49,240
Yuxiu? What's wrong?

466
00:38:49,600 --> 00:38:50,801
It's urgent. Listen to me.

467
00:38:51,640 --> 00:38:54,080
A student's parent wants to report me
for forging my identity.

468
00:38:54,441 --> 00:38:55,361
I have to go.

469
00:38:55,961 --> 00:38:56,792
Where are you going?

470
00:38:57,401 --> 00:38:59,720
I've saved some money.
Let me get it for you.

471
00:39:00,481 --> 00:39:02,160
No, keep it.

472
00:39:02,401 --> 00:39:04,160
You'll need the money out there.

473
00:39:04,720 --> 00:39:06,801
I can work. I can earn money anywhere.

474
00:39:07,160 --> 00:39:08,600
You have kids to look after.

475
00:39:08,961 --> 00:39:13,200
Tomorrow at noon, the bun shop
opposite to the bank on Shengli Street.

476
00:39:13,321 --> 00:39:15,281
Meet me there. I have to go.

477
00:39:18,961 --> 00:39:20,560
Tomorrow at noon.

478
00:39:25,640 --> 00:39:27,520
(Qidaohezi, 2023)
The next day at noon,

479
00:39:30,401 --> 00:39:32,001
I went to wait for her at the bun shop.

480
00:39:34,001 --> 00:39:37,481
I waited for three days straight,
but she never came.

481
00:39:42,361 --> 00:39:46,520
Wen Yuxiu promised to bring you money,
but someone else took it.

482
00:39:47,401 --> 00:39:50,761
She was probably
forcibly taken away by Hao Ying.

483
00:39:52,961 --> 00:39:55,361
But how did her husband find her?

484
00:40:00,080 --> 00:40:04,160
You told her husband
she would withdraw the money, right?

485
00:40:06,001 --> 00:40:07,921
Men die for wealth.
Birds perish for food.

486
00:40:09,688 --> 00:40:11,768
(Qidaohezi, 2004,
Agricultural Cooperative Bank)

487
00:40:14,200 --> 00:40:14,700
Wen Yuxiu.

488
00:40:19,401 --> 00:40:19,901
Get her.

489
00:40:23,281 --> 00:40:23,781
Don't run.

490
00:40:24,281 --> 00:40:26,441
Go away! Someone help!

491
00:40:26,560 --> 00:40:30,921
Go away! Help!

492
00:40:33,600 --> 00:40:35,100
Move. Get in the van.

493
00:40:46,240 --> 00:40:47,921
I'll catch you no matter where you run.

494
00:41:24,560 --> 00:41:26,720
The complaint letter
was just your backup plan.

495
00:41:27,640 --> 00:41:30,680
It was your alternative plan
in case she didn't run away.

496
00:41:31,961 --> 00:41:36,200
Your first choice
was to inform her husband,

497
00:41:37,401 --> 00:41:39,640
the man she had struggled
to escape from.

498
00:41:40,401 --> 00:41:41,921
You wanted him to take her back

499
00:41:43,640 --> 00:41:44,560
and beat her up.

500
00:41:45,680 --> 00:41:47,680
You let that man take her away.

501
00:41:48,240 --> 00:41:50,401
So no one would ever know her real name.

502
00:41:52,600 --> 00:41:54,640
You didn't give anyone
a chance to save her.

503
00:41:56,881 --> 00:41:59,600
I just made her go back
to where she came from.

504
00:42:01,401 --> 00:42:02,560
That's her destiny.

505
00:42:05,281 --> 00:42:07,720
Besides, she brought it on herself
by being greedy.

506
00:42:08,801 --> 00:42:12,441
If she hadn't been after that money,
she wouldn't have been caught.

507
00:42:14,640 --> 00:42:18,281
You blocked
every possible way out for her.

508
00:42:20,001 --> 00:42:21,240
You're vicious.

509
00:42:22,640 --> 00:42:25,200
Are you blaming me for her sake now?

510
00:42:26,520 --> 00:42:27,160
Is that so?

511
00:42:29,321 --> 00:42:30,281
I've said it before.

512
00:42:32,040 --> 00:42:33,080
She deserves it.

513
00:42:37,080 --> 00:42:41,361
Did she think about me
when she took you to the entrance exam?

514
00:42:42,600 --> 00:42:43,801
Did she ever pity me?

515
00:42:44,921 --> 00:42:49,921
Was it my fault that she was poor
and married a man who beat her?

516
00:42:51,881 --> 00:42:55,160
